## Core Concepts

### ECS Mandates
- **Entities**: IDs only (no methods)
- **Components**: Pure @dataclass, immutable, no logic
- **Systems**: Pure functions (DataFrame → DataFrame)
- **Resources**: Stateful objects; store IDs not instances
- **Data-Oriented**: SoA over AoS, hot/cold split

### DataFrame Storage (MANDATED)
All ECS entity stores: Polars `DataFrame` (no dict/list/class)
System signature: `def system_name(entity_store: pl.DataFrame) -> pl.DataFrame`

### Multi-Store Systems
- Systems may accept multiple DataFrames: `(entity_store, cache_store, other_store)`
- External resources injected via `Optional[Resource] = None`
- Return tuple when cache updated: `Tuple[pl.DataFrame, pl.DataFrame]`
- Primary store always first in signature and return

### DataFrame Patterns
- Copy-on-write before modification
- Guards: `if entity_store.is_empty(): return entity_store`, early return if columns missing
- Vectorization only (no row loops)
- Type-annotate all DataFrame params/returns

### Cache DataFrame Pattern
- Use a dedicated cache DataFrame, never globals or `@lru_cache`
- Pass cache as explicit param+return: `(entity_store, cache_store) -> (updated_store, updated_cache)`
- Keep cache separate from business data; no module-level dicts

### Storage Decision
- Polars: dense data (>100 entities, analytics)
- esper: sparse, event-driven only

### Prohibited
Entity/component methods, system side effects, resource instances in DataFrames, global cache state, non-DataFrame storage, in-place mutation, row loops, missing guards

